The Vlocity batch framework lets you run an Integration Procedure or Vlocity OpenInterface on a schedule. Typical use cases are a recurrent billing cycle or a scan for insurance policies that come up for renewal in the next 60 days.

Batch Actions and Scheduled Jobs are available in OmniStudio if the OmniStudio package was installed before the Salesforce Industries package was installed.

The input can be one of the following:

* Null: The Integration Procedure or VlocityOpenInterface finds data using its Actions or methods.
* SOQL query: The result of a static query is the input.
* JSON data with merge fields: The Integration Procedure is called by a business process that has contextual data.

To define the jobs to be run, you add records to the Vlocity Scheduled Job custom object. To launch scheduled jobs, you can:

* Run the Vlocity batch framework
* Launch jobs programmatically
* Use a Batch Action in an Integration Procedure

The Vlocity batch framework launches the jobs that are defined in the Vlocity Scheduled Job custom object. To start the Vlocity batch framework, you must execute Apex code.

You can use VlocityBatchFramework methods to start scheduled jobs with a Data Source Type of Query. You can also invoke an Integration Procedure or VlocityOpenInterface as a job.

To create batch jobs, go to the Vlocity Scheduled Jobs tab and add a record by clicking New. Then specify the settings you need in the Vlocity Scheduled Job fields.

Note that this article is about Batch Jobs for Integration Procedures and Vlocity Open Interfaces.
title: Batch Jobs for Integration Procedures and Vlocity Open Interfaces
